60|$|It {{is true that}} <b>we</b> <b>had</b> <b>always</b> been {{prepared}} for winter, wherever <b>we</b> <b>had</b> lived; {{but this was a}} different case. In other days it did not matter much whether we were ready or not; but now our house, our cow, our poultry, and indeed ourselves, might have suffered,--there is no way of finding out exactly how much,--if <b>we</b> <b>had</b> not made all possible preparations for the coming of cold weather.|$|R
